kshaft Timing Pin","Timing hole in crankcase","The plunger of the camshaft drive chain tensioner is under spring tension. Always wear hand, eye and facial protection when removing the tensioner as unprotected areas of the body can be injured if the spring tension is released in an unexpected or uncontrolled way.","If installing a new hydraulic tensioner, do not release the plunger before fitting.","If installing the original hydraulic tensioner, the engine oil must be drained out of the tensioner to enable the plunger to be reset and locked into position at the snap ring groove.","Support ","service tool T3880420"," in a soft jawed vice.","Prior to fitting the hydraulic adjuster to ","service tool T3880420"," make sure the rubber pad is fitted into the tip of the service tool.","Rubber pad","Tip","Fit the hydraulic tensioner to the adaptor of ","service tool T3880420"," as shown in the illustration below.","Hydraulic tensioner","Adaptor","Turn the handle of ","service tool T3880420"," clockwise until the tip contacts the plunger.","Tip","Plunger","Continue to turn the handle clockwise until the snap ring aligns with the snap ring groove.","Snap ring","Snap ring groove","Make sure the snap ring is in its groove and slowly turn the handle anticlockwise. Make sure the plunger is held in place.","Remove the hydraulic tensioner from ","service tool T3880420",".","Fit a new gasket to the hydraulic tensioner.","Fit the tensioner to the cylinder head as noted for removal and tighten the fixings to ","10 Nm",".","Fixings","Camshaft drive chain tensioner","Gasket","Remove the two wedges that are between the camshaft sprockets and the crankcase.","Remove ","service tool T3880422",".","T3880422 - Crankshaft Timing Pin","Timing hole in crankcase","To release the plunger from the snap ring holding the hydraulic tensioner, check that the tensioner plunger is correctly located in the middle of the camshaft drive chain tensioner blade when viewed from above.","Using a suitable flat 